    <text id="B0552T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>How writes about how best he may procure his needed supplies.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr> Geo. Q. White <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Quartermaster">A.Q.M.</abbr><lb/><abbr
                            expan="Chief Quartermaster">C.Q.M.</abbr>
                        <unclear>T.F.A.</unclear> Richmond <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-12-21"><abbr expan="December">Dec</abbr> 21st 1865</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Captain</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of your communication of the 18th in
                    Reference to Requisitions, and in reply I have respectfully to state that I have
                    not construed the order referred to in the manner which I now see is implied.</p>

                <p>Respecting the requisitions already approved I have to communicate the
                    information that stores can probably be most readily obtained from the Depot at
                    Harpers Ferry, as I understand there is an accumulation of <abbr
                        expan="Quartermaster">QM</abbr> Property there under the care of <abbr
                        expan="Brevet Major">Bt. Maj.</abbr> Geo A. Flagg <abbr
                        expan="Assistant Quartermaster">A.Q.M.</abbr> (from whom the transportation
                    can certainly be best procurred) and I think he can better furnish the wood
                    which I thought to get delivered at the offices of the several <abbr
                        expan="Assistant Superintendents">Asst. Supts.</abbr> and have it paid for
                    in <unclear>Form 12</unclear> by Maj. Flagg, who would then issue it to me. I
                    have therefore respectfully to request that the approved requisitions may be
                    forwarded to me in order that I may attempt in this way to obtain the much
                    needed stores.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am &amp;c</salute>
                    <signed>WSH<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp;c</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
